parameters.query:
UPDATE invoice_client_embeddings
SET text = CONCAT(
              'Invoice Client Name: ', text, E'\n',
              'Invoice Client Number: ', metadata->>'client_number', E'\n',
              'Address: ', metadata->>'address'
           ),
    metadata = (metadata::jsonb) - 'address'
WHERE metadata->>'book_number' = $1
  AND metadata->>'client_number' = $2

This letter, when signed by Chief Little Moon, Inc. ("CLM") and Alexander Goldblatt p/k/a "Alex Goldblatt" (CLM and Alex Goldblatt shall sometimes be individually and collectively referred to herein as "you"), on the one hand, and by Lizzo, LLC ("we" or "us"), on the other hand, will constitute our agreement ("Agreement") with regard to you furnishing the non-exclusive services of, respectively, Jasper Harris and Alex Goldblatt (Jasper Harris and Alex Goldblatt shall sometimes be individually and collectively referred to herein as the "Producer") in connection with one (1) master recording of the musical composition tentatively entitled "STILL CANT FUH" (the "Master") embodying the performances of Melissa Jefferson p/k/a "Lizzo" ("Artist") for, among other exploitations, possible inclusion on Artist's forthcoming mixtape album (the "Album") to be delivered by Artist to Nice Life Recording Company c/o Atlantic Records ("Record Company") pursuant to Artist's agreement with Record Company ("Recording Agreement"), dated as of December 15, 2015 (as may be hereafter amended), for the manufacture and distribution of phonograph records and other uses of the Master.

# 1. Services: 

(a) You will cause Producer to furnish to us such services as are reasonably necessary to produce, record and edit the Master pursuant to a production schedule designated and approved by us. In the event that you and/or Producer render services as a musician, vocalist or other performer in connection with the Master, such services shall be included in your services as a producer hereunder (including the consideration therefor). As of the date of execution hereof, subject to our rights in the event of your and/or Producer's breach of any warranty and/or representation made by you and/or Producer hereunder and/or Producer's failure to comply with your and/or Producer's obligations hereunder, we acknowledge the timely and satisfactory completion of the services required to be rendered by you in connection with the Master and your delivery and our acceptance of such satisfactory Master hereunder.
(b) The Master (together with the performances embodied thereon and the services provided hereunder, as well as any and all derivative works created therefrom and reproductions made thereof, but excluding the underlying musical composition embodied thereon) shall, from the inception of its creation, be considered a "work made for hire" for Record Company within the meaning of the Copyright Act of 1976 (Title 17, U.S.C.), as amended. If it is determined that the Master does not so qualify, then such Master, together with all rights therein (including the sound recording copyright and all renewals and
extensions thereof, but excluding the copyright in the underlying musical composition embodied thereon), shall be automatically assigned to Record Company by this Agreement. Nevertheless, you shall, upon our reasonable request, execute and deliver to us, and cause any or all persons furnished and/or engaged solely by you and/or Producer rendering services hereunder, to execute and deliver to us any assignments of copyright (including renewals and extensions thereof) in and to the Master as we may deem necessary, and you hereby appoint us as your and Producer's limited attorney-in-fact solely for the purpose of executing such assignments in our name in the event that you and/or Producer fail to execute the same after being given the first opportunity to do so within five (5) business days of our delivery of such documents to you (and we shall send you copies of such assignments executed by us hereunder). The Master (but excluding the underlying musical composition embodied thereon) shall, from the inception of its creation, be entirely our property in perpetuity, throughout the world, free of any claim whatsoever by you, Producer or by any persons deriving any rights or interests therefrom. Without limiting the generality of the preceding sentence, Record Company and us, and Record Company's and our designees, as the case may be, shall have the exclusive unrestricted worldwide and perpetual right to use, distribute, sell and exploit the Master in any and all media.
(c) You shall cause Producer to deliver fully edited and leadered stereophonic master recordings to Record Company not later than a date to be specified by us in consultation with you, together with all necessary licenses, approvals, consents and permissions arising out of your and/or Producer's sole activities, if any. Your submission of the Master shall constitute your representation that you and/or Producer have obtained all such material for which you and/or Producer are solely responsible for. The Master shall be subject to the approval of us and/or Record Company as technically and commercially satisfactory for the manufacture and sale of phonograph records. In the event that the Master is not technically and commercially satisfactory, you shall, upon our and/or Record Company's request, cause Producer to re-record and/or re-produce such Master until a Master technically and commercially satisfactory to us and/or Record Company has been obtained.
(d) You shall cause Producer to perform all such services as are customarily performed by producers in the recording industry, including without limitation and subject to paragraph 2 below, engaging musicians, vocalists, conductors, contractors, arrangers and copyists, and arranging for the use of recording studios and other necessary technical facilities and personnel solely in connection with your and/or Producer's services hereunder. You and/or Producer shall be responsible for the preparation and submission of all necessary union forms and session reports, if applicable to the services rendered by you and Producer hereunder, to enable us to timely and properly complete and file all such documentation. You shall be responsible for late payment penalties with respect to such documentation if such penalties are incurred due to solely your and/or Producer's acts and/or omissions. As of the date of execution hereof, subject to our rights in the event of your and/or Producer's breach of any warranty and/or representation made by you and/or Producer hereunder and/or Producer's failure to comply with your and/or Producer's obligations hereunder, we hereby acknowledge that there are no such late payment penalties hereunder incurred due to your and/or Producer's acts and/or omissions.
(e) You and Producer hereby acknowledge and agree that any dissemination or threatened dissemination of the Master or any portion thereof prior to the authorized release of a phonograph record containing such Master or any portion thereof may necessarily result in irreparable harm and injury to us for which no adequate remedy is available at law and which is not fully compensable in money damages alone, and that we shall, therefore, in the event of any such unauthorized dissemination, or threat thereof, be entitled to seek injunctive (and any other equitable) relief as may be necessary to prevent, remedy and/or mitigate the adverse effects of such actual or threatened dissemination, in addition to any legal remedies (including damages to which we may be entitled and the recovery of court costs and attorneys' fees reasonably incurred in connection with obtaining such relief). CLM and Alex Goldblatt each expressly agree that, solely on their own behalf and on behalf of their respective Producer, without limiting any other rights or remedies we may have, we shall be entitled to recover any and all monies or other benefits whatsoever received by CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt from any and all sources in connection with any
unauthorized use or dissemination by or on behalf of CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt (as applicable) of the Master or any portion thereof, and that any such monies or other benefits so received by CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt (as applicable) shall be held in trust by CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt (as applicable) for immediate payment to Artist. The provisions of this paragraph 1(e) are material terms of this Agreement. As of the date of execution hereof, subject to our rights in the event of your and/or Producer's breach of any warranty and/or representation made by you and/or Producer hereunder and/or your and/or Producer's failure to comply with your and/or Producer's obligations hereunder, to our knowledge, we hereby acknowledge that you have complied with this paragraph 1(e).

# 2. Recording Procedure: 

The recording budget for the Master (including the "Fee" and "Advance" payable to you pursuant to paragraph 3 below) shall be determined by us in consultation with you (the "Approved Budget"), subject to the approval of the Record Company. You shall be responsible for all recording costs incurred in excess of the Approved Budget solely to the extent such overages are caused by your and/or Producer's acts and/or omissions. In the event we and/or Record Company pay any costs described in the immediately preceding sentence, you shall be responsible for such costs so paid by us and/or Record Company, and you shall promptly reimburse us and/or Record Company therefor upon demand. Any sums paid by us and/or Record Company and not promptly reimbursed by you as provided in this paragraph may, at our and/or Record Company's sole election and without limiting our and/or Record Company's rights, be applied by us and/or Record Company in reduction of any royalties or other sums payable to you under this Agreement (excluding mechanical royalties and/or Direct Monies [as hereafter defined]). Nothing contained in this Agreement shall obligate us to permit the continuation of any recording session or project if we reasonably anticipate that the costs will exceed those specified in the Approved Budget or that the Master being produced and/or mixed will not be technically and commercially satisfactory. As of the date of execution hereof, subject to our rights in the event of your and/or Producer's breach of any warranty and/or representation made by you and/or Producer hereunder and/or Producer's failure to comply with your and/or Producer's obligations hereunder, we hereby acknowledge approval of the Approved Budget and that there are no excess costs incurred and/or paid by us and/or Record Company for which you and/or Producer are responsible hereunder.

## 3. Fee / Advance:

In consideration of the services rendered by you and Producer hereunder, we hereby agree to pay you a sum in the amount of Five Thousand Dollars $(\$ 5,000.00)$ for the Master delivered and accepted hereunder (the "Fee"), fifty percent (50\%) of which shall constitute a recoupable advance for the Master produced and delivered hereunder (the "Advance"). The Fee shall be payable promptly following the complete execution and delivery to us of this Agreement. For the avoidance of doubt, the Advance shall constitute an advance hereunder and shall be recoupable from any record royalties payable to you hereunder (excluding mechanical royalties and/or Direct Monies). The Fee and Advance shall be inclusive of and deemed a pre-payment of compensation for your and Producer's services, if any, as a performer (e.g., musician, vocalist, etc.) in connection with the Master, which shall be equivalent to the applicable minimum union scale.

## 4. Royalties:

(a) Provided you and/or Producer are not in uncured, material breach of any of your and/or Producer's obligations hereunder, we will pay to you (or instruct and use reasonable efforts to cause Record Company to pay to you on our behalf, pursuant to an irrevocable letter of direction in substantially the form attached hereto as Exhibit "A" [the "Letter of Direction"]) a royalty calculated at a basic royalty rate of three and one-third percent (3.33\%) (the "Basic Rate"), pro-rated as provided below, of the Royalty Base Price with respect to top-line, full priced net sales of the Album consisting entirely of the Master recorded hereunder through normal retail channels in the United States ("USNRC Net Sales"). We hereby
acknowledge that Producer's royalty set forth in this paragraph and the relevant provisions of the Recording Agreement pursuant to which such royalty is calculated and adjusted (as described in paragraph 4(b)(i) below) shall be no less favorable to Producer than that applicable to the other producer entitled to receive a record royalty for such other producer's production contribution to the Master.
(b) (i) The royalty payable to you shall be calculated, determined, reduced, adjusted and paid (but not escalated as a result of sales) in the same manner (e.g., reductions and adjustments to royalty rates, free goods, Royalty Base Price, reserves, DAT and other format-based adjustments, etc.) and subject to the same terms and conditions as Artist's royalties are calculated, determined, reduced, adjusted and paid pursuant to the Recording Agreement (but without regards to the Company's and/or Artist's overall recoupment status with Record Company). The royalty payable to you for singles, new technologies, foreign sales and other sales of records derived from, or uses of, the Master embodied on the Album will be reduced and pro-rated in the same proportion, if any, as Artist's basic royalties are reduced and pro-rated under the Recording Agreement. With respect to sales or uses of the Master for which Artist receives a royalty which is computed as a percentage of Record Company's net receipts, net monies, flat fees or the like (which may include monies derived from the exploitation of so-called "NFTs" incorporating the Master for which Artist receives such monies, if applicable), your royalty hereunder in respect of such sale or use shall be equal to Artist's royalty therefor multiplied by a fraction (the "Fraction"), the numerator of which is equal to the Basic Rate, and the denominator of which is equal to Artist's basic, unescalated "all-in" royalty rate for USNRC Net Sales of top-line albums.
(ii) For the avoidance of doubt, the immediately preceding sentence shall apply to any royalties directly attributable solely to the use or exploitation of the Master produced hereunder (and not the musical compositions embodied thereon) which such royalties are received directly by or credited directly to Artist from a third party other than Record Company (e.g., monies from SoundExchange), and your share of such royalties shall be paid to you in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement solely to the extent that you have not received your pro-rata share of such royalties directly (collectively, "Direct Monies"). Pursuant to irrevocable letters of direction in the form attached hereto as Exhibit "B", we shall instruct SoundExchange to account and pay directly to you Producer's share (i.e., our royalty multiplied by the Fraction) of any digital performance royalties payable directly to us by SoundExchange which are solely, directly and identifiably attributable to the Master produced hereunder (and not the musical compositions embodied thereon). In the event that any record embodying the Master featuring the performances of Artist with another musical side artist(s) is released, we shall instruct and use reasonable efforts to cause such side artist(s) to execute SoundExchange letter(s) of direction authorizing the direct payment of Producer's share thereof to you. Solely in the event that SoundExchange fails or refuses to so account to you such share pursuant to such letter of direction and solely to the extent that SoundExchange has rendered statements and actually paid Producer's share of such digital performance royalties to Artist directly, then we shall send you Producer's share of such SoundExchange royalties as set forth hereunder (at your cost and expense for any wire or processing fees or the like, if any), within forty five (45) days following our receipt of such applicable monies from SoundExchange. In so accounting to you in accordance with this paragraph, we shall have the right to rely on statements rendered to us by SoundExchange.
(c) As to records not consisting entirely of the Master produced by Producer hereunder, the royalty rate otherwise payable to you hereunder with respect to any sales of such record shall be pro-rated by multiplying such royalty rate by a fraction, the numerator of which is the number of Masters embodied on such record and the denominator of which is the total number of royalty-bearing master recordings (including the Master) embodied thereon. Notwithstanding the foregoing: (i) with respect to the commercial release in the United States of any single record solely embodying the Master hereunder as the so-called "A" side and another master recording not produced by Producer as the so-called "B" side, your royalty hereunder in respect of such sales of such single shall not be pro-rated pursuant to the immediately preceding sentence due to the fact that the Master recording embodied on such "B" side was not produced by Producer; and (ii) with respect to the commercial release in the United States of any single record embodying the Master hereunder
as the so-called "B" side and another master recording not produced by Producer as the so-called "A" side, you shall not be entitled to any royalty hereunder in respect of such sales of such single in the event that the producer of the master recording embodied on the so-called "A" side is entitled to so-called "A-side protection" with respect thereto.
(d) In the event that the Master is produced by Producer with another producer to whom we or Record Company are obligated to pay a royalty, or in the event any other individual to whom we or Record Company shall be obligated to pay a royalty shall perform additional services with respect to such Master produced by Producer hereunder, then the royalty payable to you hereunder with respect to such Master shall not be reduced by the royalty payable by Record Company or us to such other individual.
(e) No royalty shall be payable to you hereunder until Record Company has recouped all recording costs (excluding the Advance payable pursuant to paragraph 3 above and any "in pocket" advances paid to us or Artist) incurred in connection with the Master from the "net artist" royalties (i.e., those royalties payable by the Record Company to Artist excluding any royalties payable to all producers and mixers, including you and Producer, who rendered services in connection with the Master) payable or credited to Artist by Record Company in respect of the Master. After recoupment of such recording costs as aforesaid, royalties shall be payable to you hereunder for all records sold and/or commercially exploited for which royalties are payable, retroactively from the first such record sold, subject to recoupment from such royalties of the Advance paid to you hereunder.
(f) With respect to audiovisual recordings embodying the Master produced hereunder ("Music Videos"), your royalty shall be equal to fifty percent ( $50 \%$ ) of the royalty payable to Artist in respect thereof, multiplied by the Fraction, and the royalty payable to you therefor shall be pro-rated as provided in paragraph 4(c) above, if applicable. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, such royalty shall be payable on a prospective basis only, after the Record Company recoups all costs which are recoupable pursuant to the Recording Agreement which are attributable to such Music Videos.

# 5. Accountings: 

(a) With respect to royalties payable to you hereunder, we shall instruct and use reasonable efforts to cause Record Company to account for and to pay directly to you, on our behalf, the royalties becoming due to you hereunder, if any (pursuant to the Letter of Direction). Any and all such statements and/or royalties shall be rendered and/or paid at the same times as Record Company is required to render statements and/or pay Artist. If Record Company fails or refuses to so account to you, we shall send you royalty statements and any payments shown thereby to be due to you after deduction of the Advance within sixty (60) days following our receipt of each statement applicable to the Master from the Record Company. In so accounting to you, we shall have the right to rely on the statements rendered to Artist by Record Company.
(b) All royalty statements and all other accountings rendered by us to you, or on our behalf, shall be binding upon you and not subject to any objection by you for any reason unless specific objection in writing, stating the basis thereof, is given to us within three (3) years from the date rendered. You shall be foreclosed from maintaining any action, claim or proceeding against us in any forum or tribunal with respect to any statement or accounting due hereunder unless such action, claim or proceeding is commenced against us in a court of competent jurisdiction within three (3) years after the date such statement or accounting is rendered.
(c) You shall have the right to appoint a certified public accountant, who is not then currently engaged in an outstanding audit of us, to examine our books and records relating to the sale and/or other commercial exploitation of records embodying the Master hereunder (but excluding any books or records relating to the manufacture of records) provided that such examination shall take place at our offices during normal business hours, on reasonable written notice, not more frequently than once in any calendar
year and at your sole cost and expense. Such examination may be conducted only once with respect to a particular statement and only within three (3) years after the date such statement is rendered. You shall cause your accountant to deliver a relevant copy of his or her audit report to us within thirty (30) days after the completion of said accountant's examination of our books and records. For the avoidance of doubt, you shall not have the right to examine Record Company's books and records. The rights granted herein to you constitute your sole right to examine our books and records.
(d) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the first sentence of paragraph 5(c) above, if we notify you that the certified public accountant designated by you to conduct an examination of our books and records under paragraph 5(c) is engaged in an examination for another person or entity ("Other Examination"), you may nevertheless have your examination conducted by your designee, and the running of the time within which such examination may be made shall be suspended until your designee has completed the Other Examination, subject to the following conditions:
(i) You shall notify us of your election to that effect within twenty (20) days after the date of our said notice to you;
(ii) Your designee shall proceed in a reasonably continuous and expeditious manner to complete the Other Examination and render the final report thereon to the client and us;
(iii) Your examination shall not be commenced by your designee before the delivery to us of the final report on the Other Examination, shall be commenced within sixty (60) days thereafter, and shall be conducted in a reasonably continuous manner; and
(iv) The suspension of time to permit your designee to conduct such audit shall not prejudice or otherwise adversely impact any rights or obligations of us and/or Artist in connection with or related to the same.

Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, the preceding provisions of this paragraph 5(d) will not apply if we elect to waive the provisions of the first sentence of paragraph 5(c) which require that your representative shall not be engaged in any Other Examination.
(e) If we conduct an audit of Record Company, we shall credit to your account hereunder a pro-rata share of any royalties received by or credited to us as a result thereof which are specifically attributable to the Master, net of your share of the total, actual, direct, verifiable, out-of-pocket, third party costs and expenses of the audit concerned (i.e., that same proportion of the total costs and expenses that such credit to you bears to the total amount of royalties received by or credited to us in connection with the audit concerned).
(f) You hereby acknowledge, agree and irrevocably direct and authorize us to remit the Fee and Basic Rate becoming payable in connection with the Master equally among each of you on behalf of each of your respective Producer.

# 6. Credit: 

You hereby irrevocably grant to us and to our designees (including, without limitation, Record Company) in perpetuity the non-exclusive right to use and publish, throughout the world, Producer's name as well as Producer's likenesses, voices and biographical materials solely in connection with the sale, promotion, marketing, advertising and exploitation of phonograph records derived from the Master produced hereunder (but it being understood that Producer's likenesses, voices and biographical materials used for such purposes shall not be used in any commercial endorsement and/or any commercial "tie-in" without your prior written consent). We shall provide you for your approval any portrait, pictures or other likeness of Producer or biographical material about Producer which we propose to use in connection therewith. We will
not use any such material which you disapprove in writing (email shall suffice) within five (5) business days following the date on which such materials are provided to you, provided you furnish substitute material, satisfactory to us in our sole and reasonable discretion, in time for use within Record Company's production and release schedules. No inadvertent, non-repetitive failure to comply with this paragraph will constitute a breach of this Agreement, and you will not be entitled to injunctive relief to restrain the continuing use of any material used in contravention of this paragraph. Upon receipt of notice from you that we have not provided such material to you for approval as set forth in this paragraph 6 , we shall use reasonable efforts to prospectively cure such failure. You shall have the right to submit photographs and likenesses of, and biographical material concerning, Producer and your submission of the same shall constitute your approval thereof. We shall instruct and use reasonable efforts to cause Record Company to accord Producer an appropriate credit on all liner notes and packaging of Albums or other records derived from the Master produced by Producer (in all configurations, to the extent such configurations provide such credits and wherever digital meta-data permits), and in any other locations where a similar credit is accorded to any other producer of the Master (in the same size, style, format and prominence as the credit accorded to any other producer of the Master). Such credit shall be in substantially the following form: "Produced by Ricky Reed, Jasper Harris, Alex Goldblatt". You and Producer hereby acknowledge that you and Producer have approved the foregoing producer credit. We shall also instruct and use reasonable efforts to cause Record Company to accord Producer such credit (in the same size, style, format and prominence as the credit accorded to any other producer of the Master) in all one-quarter ( $1 / 4$ ) page or larger trade advertisements (and, to the extent permitted by Record Company's standard policies, all one-quarter (1/4) page or larger advertisements for consumer publications and so-called Billboard "strip" ads), which relate to singles embodying the Master hereunder on the A-side, in the United States placed by or under Record Company's control. Our inadvertent, non-repetitive failure to comply with the foregoing provisions shall not constitute a breach of this Agreement. Upon receipt of notice from you (email shall suffice) that Producer has not been accorded credit as set forth in this paragraph 6, we shall instruct and use reasonable efforts to cause Record Company to prospectively cure any failure to accord such credit (and promptly with respect to metadata).

# 7. Controlled Compositions: 

(a) As used in this Agreement, "Controlled Composition" shall mean, with respect to the musical composition embodied on the Master hereunder (the "Subject Composition"), those portions of the Subject Composition: (i) which are written or composed by you and/or Producer, (ii) which are owned or controlled, directly or indirectly, by you and/or Producer (and/or your and/or Producer's designee(s)) or by any person owned, controlled or affiliated with you and/or Producer (and/or your and/or Producer's designee(s)), or (iii) in which you and/or Producer (and/or your and/or Producer's designee(s)) have a direct or indirect income or other interest of any nature or sort. You and Producer shall, and shall cause your and Producer's respective licensees, designees and affiliates to, grant licenses to us and Record Company (and our respective licensees, designees, affiliates, distributors and assigns) for the right to reproduce, use or otherwise exploit the Controlled Composition in recordings or otherwise (including, without limitation, any and all versions and/or remixes of the Subject Composition) featuring Artist, in any and all configurations in any and all media throughout the universe, in accordance with, and subject to, all of the terms and conditions as are contained in the Recording Agreement applicable to compositions written by Artist; except that, for the purpose of computing the mechanical royalties hereunder in respect of the Controlled Composition, the so-called mechanical royalty "cap" set forth in the Recording Agreement shall not apply, and the mechanical royalty rate payable to you in respect of USNRC Net Sales of top-line, full-priced albums embodying the Controlled Composition shall equal one hundred percent ( $100 \%$ ) of the minimum compulsory license rate in the United States and Canada (as applicable) as of delivery of the applicable version of the Master for which the mechanical royalty is paid. CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt (as applicable) shall be responsible to obligate any other persons furnished and/or engaged solely by CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt, respectively, to be bound by the provisions contained in Sections 7 and 9 of this Agreement, and CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt (as applicable) shall cause all persons furnished and/or engaged solely by CLM, Jasper Harris or Alex Goldblatt, respectively, to execute and deliver an agreement evidencing the same, which is deemed to be a material term of this Agreement.
(b) Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, you and Producer shall grant, and shall cause your and Producer's respective licensees, designees and affiliates to grant, synchronization licenses, free of charge, authorizing the use of the Controlled Composition (including the music and lyrics thereof) in so-called "promotional" audiovisual recordings featuring Artist (and which audiovisual recordings may visually display all or some of the lyrics of the Controlled Composition) for the worldwide exploitation of such promotional audiovisual recordings in all media whether now known or hereafter devised throughout the universe, for which neither Artist nor our and/or Artist's designee(s) receives any compensation for the same.
